---

## 🎯 Functional Requirements

* Send notifications using templates
* Support real-time and scheduled notifications
* User preference management
* Delivery status tracking

---

## ⚙️ Non-Functional Requirements

* Scale: 1M requests/min
* High availability > consistency
* Low latency for OTP notifications
* Fault tolerance and retry handling

---

## 🧩 System Components

### API Gateway

* Handles routing, rate limiting, and load balancing

### Notification Service

* Accepts client requests and pushes events to Kafka

### Kafka

* Enables asynchronous processing
* Topics categorized by priority (critical, standard, promotional)

### Preference Service

* Stores user channel preferences
* Uses Redis cache for fast reads

### Template Service

* Manages notification templates

### Status Service

* Tracks delivery status asynchronously

### External Providers

* SMS → Twilio
* Email → Amazon SES
* Push → FCM/APNS

---

## 🔁 Reliability Design

### Retry Mechanism

* Failed messages are retried using exponential backoff

### Dead Letter Queue (DLQ)

* Messages failing after max retries are moved to DLQ

### Idempotency

* Prevents duplicate notifications during retries

---

## ⚖️ Trade-offs

* Chose **Kafka (async)** over sync calls → better scalability but slightly higher latency
* Availability prioritized over strong consistency
* Separate topics per priority → better control but higher complexity

---

## 🚧 Future Improvements

* Scheduler service for delayed notifications
* Fanout service for bulk notifications
* OTP fast-path (bypass Kafka)
* Observability (metrics, logging, alerting)

---

## 🧠 Key Learnings

* Designing scalable event-driven systems
* Handling failures using retry & DLQ
* Managing trade-offs in distributed systems

